<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>It's going to be a problem, possible solutions</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:41 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> It's going to be a problem, possible solutions<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=782" TARGET=_self>Possible Body guarding</A> (Tallina)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Two good ways to solve this problem:
<P>#1 When you die, the player that killed you (or group) can loot one item. All remaining items appear on your body when you ressurect (advantage of being PvP).
<P>#2 You can use the /consent function to let a friend loot it. Ok if you have blue players who can loot you, but no help at all on a PvP server.
<P>#3 You are immune to attacks for X minutes after you return from the dead unless you attack another player first. Upon looting your corpse you have 3 minutes remaining of immunity before you can be attacked again (so you can run for the zone).
<P>#2 is the existing system but won't work for the PvP server. I prefer #1 but Verant might think that is favoring PVP players too much to give them their items back (or it's not realistic enough). I think #1 would be simpler to implement and solves the problem thoroughly.
<P>Note don't anyone even bother posting that camping is a good feature or I'll whip out my Flame Thrower!
<P>&gt; I have a serious concern about dieing after a skirmish then
<BR>&gt; coming to retreive my stuff and being ambushed by people just to
<BR>&gt; take another item..
<P>&gt; Dunno if it was addressed somewhere but It would really piss me
<BR>&gt; off...
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
